ZCZC GE62
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 072300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A SLOW-MOV AND FLN LOW IS LIKELY TO BE NEAR NERN FORTIES
1003 WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE COVERING MUCH OF FRANCE AND GERMANY. BY
EARLY AFTERNOON ON TUESDAY THE LOW IS FCST TO BE NEAR VIKING 1007 WITH A
RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING N FM IRELAND TO ICELAND. THIS RIDGE WILL
MOV EWARDS TO REACH FAR WERN WATERS OF CULLERCOATS BY EARLY WEDNESDAY WITH
THE LOW LOSING ITS IDENTITY ACROSS SERN NORWAY. THE RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
WILL CONTINUE TO DRIFT EWARDS ACROSS ALL CULLERCOATS WATERS WITH A WEAK FRONT
PROBABLY FLW. DURING THURSDAY THIS FRONT WILL CLEAR EWARDS WITH PRESSURE
BLDN ACROSS MOST WATERS OF CULLERCOATS FM THE SE. AN ANTICYCLONE MAY BECOME
CENTRED OVER THE CZECH REPUBLIC 1025 BY EVENING. NO GALES OR STRG WINDS ARE
EXP TO AFFECT CULLERCOATS DURING THE PERIOD
